by Western Fardelshufflestein » Sat Apr 24, 2021 10:55 am

One of my problems is that I find writing about Alastair and his struggles so interesting, and my brain has fixated on that enough that I'm lowkey writing a serial over here. Like, Marie definitely has potential--going from having her husband by her side to being the sole executive of an entire country is definitely an intriguing premise. And her personality (she's heccin' anxious and a total Gryffindor, but not stereotypically "heroic/chivalrous/hates Slytherin" way because, like, who says she's even read the HP books?) also adds to her interestingness. But whenever I write her, she's grieving, in a way, over what happened to Alastair. I guess I'd be the same way in her position, but it isn't like she's doing nothing but feel horribly about him. She has to make sure WF doesn't become a total dumpster fire.

As for Wil, well, he's got a prodigal son-type past that is in my head, but I haven't expanded upon it in writing.

Addendum: KG, when did your sig get so GOOD?
